A prospective Joint Admissions and Matriculation Board, JAMB, candidate from Government Science Secondary School, Birnin-Gwari in Kaduna State has been killed by terrorists.. Terrorists Kill JAMB Prospective Candidate, 7 Others, Kidnap 57 In Kaduna The victim was on his way to register for UTME, in Kaduna, when he was attacked by the terrorists. He escaped with a bullet wound, but died later. Ibrahim Abubakar Nagwari, Chairman, Birnin Gwari Vanguard for Security and Good Governance, in a statement, explained that the terrorists killed 7 locals in the community. He lamented the resurgence of violence in the area, saying that it had become a daily experience to the locals that are being terrorised by the terrorists. He further explained that three other people escaped with mild wounds, adding that 57 others were abducted. According to him, “the nightmare of armed banditry along Birnin-Gwari-Kaduna highway has further deteriorated in the last twenty-four hours.”  Source Some bandits have abducted four persons that included three JAMB candidates who sat for the Saturday’s Unified Tertiary Joint Matriculations Examination in Kaduna State. The police in Kaduna, on Monday, confirmed the incident. The police said the four were kidnapped at Ungwan Yako Village, Birni Gwari Local Government Area of… In "News" Kaduna State government has confirmed that bandits shot at the official vehicle of Emir of Birnin-Gwari around the Zonkoro axis of the Kaduna-Birnin Gwari road, within Chikun local. The State Commissioner of Internal Security and Home Affairs, Samuel Aruwan confirmed the incident in a statement, saying that, the incident happened… In "News" The Nigerian Army said, yesterday, that troops of Operation Hadarin Daji thwarted a kidnap attempt by bandits, killing scores of them, at Kabasa village in Magami Local Government Area (LGA) of Zamfara State. The Director of Army Public Relations, Brig.-Gen. Mohammed Yerima, said that troops of Sector 3 army unit… In "News"